title: A29 autoroute
text:
The A 29 is a major toll motorway in <a href="Normandy">Normandy</a> and <a href="Picardy">Picardy</a>, northwestern and northern <a href="France">France</a>. The road is also part of <a href="European%20route%20E44">European route E44</a>. From its western interchange with the <a href="A28%20autoroute">A28 autoroute</a> until its junction with the <a href="A26%20autoroute">A26 autoroute</a>, part of the A29 also forms the northern section of the <a href="Grand%20contournement%20de%20Paris">Grand contournement de Paris</a>.
Route.
The road connects the port of <a href="Le%20Havre">Le Havre</a> with the <a href="A26%20autoroute">A 26</a> at <a href="Saint-Quentin%2C%20Aisne">Saint-Quentin</a>. It also has junctions with the <a href="A13%20autoroute">A 13</a>, <a href="A131%20autoroute">A 131</a>, <a href="A16%20autoroute">A 16</a>, <a href="A28%20autoroute">A 28</a>, and <a href="A1%20autoroute%20%28France%29">A 1</a> autoroutes.
